Created ghui_vs_adotui_analysis.md

The full analysis report is in the artifact. Here's the **TL;DR of what's missing in adotui**:

### 🔴 Critical Gaps (must-have for a usable code review tool)
1. **PR Comments** — Can't read, write, or reply to comments at all
2. **Review Submission** — Only simple vote, no review body text
3. **CI/CD Runs View** — No Azure Pipelines visibility

### 🟡 Important Gaps
4. **Issues/Work Items** — No work item viewing
5. **Split Diff View** — Type exists but not implemented
6. **Syntax Highlighting** — ghui has per-filetype highlighting in diffs
7. **Modal System** — ghui has 12 purpose-built modals; adotui uses inline y/n
8. **Command Palette** — ghui has fuzzy-search command palette vs basic text input
9. **Filtering** — No runtime search/filter on PRs
10. **Caching** — ghui has 35KB cache service; adotui re-fetches everything each time

### 🏗️ Architecture Gap
The biggest structural difference: **ghui is modular** (30 hooks, 15 services, atom-based state, context-specific keymaps) while **adotui is monolithic** — the entire app is a single 1073-line `App.tsx` with all state, handlers, and actions inline.

Let me know which features you want to prioritize implementing!